    PixAddPatientFeed.PixAddPatientFeedBuilder
    HuskyService.createPixAddPatientFeed(Destination destination, org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Organization scopingOrganization)
    This method will start building a PixAddPatientFeed, which allows the user to create a new Patient in the system.
    The properties of an FhirPatient are used as a template and expected to be filled.
    PixMergePatientFeed.PixMergePatientFeedBuilder
    HuskyService.createPixMergePatientFeed(Destination destination, org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Organization scopingOrganization, String obsolatePatientId, String homeCommunityOID, String homeCommunityNamespace)
    Use this method to build a PixMergePatientFeed, with which the user can merge two know patient objects into one in case those two are the same person.
    This case is mostly used to correct user errors when the same person is entered into a system multiple times and needs to be merged into one.
    PixPatientIDQuery.PixPatientIDQueryBuilder
    HuskyService.createPixPatientIDQuery(Destination destination)
    Use this method to build a PixPatientIDQuery, where the user can ask for all IDs known of a patient.
    PixUpdatePatientFeed.PixUpdatePatientFeedBuilder
    HuskyService.createPixUpdatePatientFeed(Destination destination, org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Organization scopingOrganization)
    This method will start building a PixUpdatePatientFeed, which allows the user to update an existing patient in the system.
    The properties of an FhirPatient are used, fill them accordingly.
    XdsRegistryStoredFindDocumentsQuery.XdsRegistryStoredFindDocumentsQueryBuilder<?,?>
    HuskyService.createRegistryStoredFindDocumentsQuery(Destination destination, Identificator patientID)
    This method will start building a XdsRegistryStoredFindDocumentsQuery, which allows the user to look for documents of a Patient identified by the ID by various parameters.
